flowRoot.flowPara: Electronics Book for Kids, Verlag: Stuttgart Frech, 1977
To roast Victims cowardly at a rangen of 500m or terrorize lodger with such scrap for "fun and profit"

The Active Denial System roast the top layer of the skin at a distance of 500m. For a range of 5 m logically more than 100 × smaller, small enough to fit in a cell phone. Actually, 1930s electron tube technology, but today you can do this also with semiconductors (Esaki-/Tunnel diode). Directly in the CPU with Army-Grade Crypto . The "Active Denial System"-denialer would thus be the natural archnemesis of an TinFoil-hat
